			<description><![CDATA[<p>
At Playnomics, we believe in an interactive gaming future.&nbsp; We see a future where connected games will be applied to all types of digital interactions, and played by all types of people on a multitude of platforms.&nbsp; Using cutting edge data analysis techniques, we are building a digital marketing platform to enable game publishers to predictively target players on a 1-1 basis. Our system presents exciting challenges such as scaling machine learning, processing large datasets in the cloud, and real time data insight. We are laying the groundwork for a future of adaptive, personalized gaming experiences, all powered by our next-generation data analytics platform.<br />
<br />
Our team is made up of smart, pragmatic entrepreneurs and technologists coming from diverse professional and academic backgrounds. Playnomics is located in the heart of San Francisco&rsquo;s vibrant SoMa district, two short blocks from Caltrain, and (pretty) close to the ballpark. We are looking for like minded talented / capable / resourceful people to join us in building the future of digital gaming. Also, to join us in grilling outside on our patio on Fridays.<br />
<br />
Software Engineer Responsibilities:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Work with senior engineers to build data processing software in Java for analyzing terabytes of data in the cloud</li>
<li>
Design, build, and maintain a real-time API for data collection and ad serving</li>
<li>
Build key components of an auction/decision system with bidding, quality analysis and accounting</li>
<li>
Work on all aspects of software development including design, implementation, testing, deployment, tuning, and monitoring</li>
<li>
Support and troubleshoot</li>
<li>
Support and troubleshoot cloud-based backend data processing infrastructure</li>
<li>
Interact with customers to integrate the product with their games and applications</li>
</ul>
<p>
What we are looking for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
BS in Computer Science (minimum)</li>
<li>
A solid foundation in Computer Science, particularly data structures, data processing, object-oriented programming, and software design</li>
<li>
Demonstrable sharp problem solving skills</li>
<li>
Excellent communications skills</li>
<li>
Expertise in Java or other object-oriented programming languages</li>
<li>
Knowledge of SQL, Hadoop, Hive or JavaScript a bonus</li>
<li>
Aptitude for Big Data and distributed/parallel systems</li>
<li>
High energy &quot;get-it-done&quot; personality</li>
</ul>
