			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About Playnomics:</strong><br />
At Playnomics, we see a future where connected games will be applied to all types of digital interactions, and played by all types of people on a multitude of platforms. Using cutting edge data analysis techniques, we continue to build out a digital marketing platform to enable game publishers to predictively target players on a 1-1 basis.</p>
<p>
Our team is made up of smart, pragmatic entrepreneurs, researchers, creative, and technologists coming from diverse professional and academic backgrounds. Playnomics main office is located in the heart of San Francisco&rsquo;s vibrant SOMA district.</p>
<p>
As the Director of Marketing for Playnomics, you will lead marketing efforts focused on driving game developer adoption of the PlayRM platform. We are looking for a candidate with experience and passion for bringing service oriented products to market in a clear and effective manner.&nbsp; A strategic thinker able to develop positioning that resonates with our customers then tactically executing go-to-market strategies that open up opportunities.</p>
<p>
For us the role is for someone who is at product person at heart - but this role is a marketing one. You need to be able to think proactively about our product and why it matters, and effectively communicate that using both paid and unpaid channels.</p>
<p>
<strong>Primary Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Develop product positioning and messaging that differentiates our product in the market</li>
<li>
Direct all product marketing activities for the company, initially as the primary resource, then growing into a team leader role</li>
<li>
Drive the creation of key marketing assets that increase new onboarding success of new customers</li>
<li>
Develop effective product marketing programs that increase developer adoption of the PlayRM platform using both paid channels and unpaid channels</li>
<li>
reate effective communication and education materials that will help the client facing teams increase usage of the PlayRM platform</li>
<li>
Own marketing insights, event coordination, education initiatives, email marketing and corporate communications</li>
<li>
Evaluate the effectiveness of product marketing programs through data driven research and analysis</li>
<li>
Communicate the value proposition of the products to the sales team and develop the sales tools that support the selling process of our products</li>
<li>
Actively participate in regular strategy sessions with sales, business development, product and account management teams to represent go-to-market needs</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
BS/BA degree preferred from top tier university, MBA a plus</li>
<li>
At least 7+ years of software marketing experience, with an emphasis on marketing technology to game developers.</li>
<li>
Experience organizing events and working with outside PR and creative agencies.</li>
<li>
Experience with quantitative measurement and evaluation frameworks</li>
<li>
Proof of ability to generate compelling marketing assets including white papers, sales collateral and go-to-market launch assets, etc.</li>
<li>
Very strong writing skills, attention to detail and an eye for quality.</li>
<li>
Excellent written, oral, and interpersonal communication skills</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Desired Attributes</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Deep knowledge of and/or experience in the mobile and gaming industries</li>
<li>
Passion for technology, start-ups, and games</li>
<li>
Excited to be a part of a dynamic industry and fast-moving company</li>
<li>
Adaptability, resourcefulness, and a positive attitude</li>
</ul>
